The paper deals with discovering the Markov blanket of a target variable from multiple interventional datasets, which involves causal inference and machine learning. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves theoretical analysis and algorithm design, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper deals with causal inference and probabilistic graphical models, which can be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
